				=09
<p>European Roulette is widely preferred due to its single zero wheel, whic=
h lowers the house edge compared to American Roulette. This guide delves de=
eply into the probabilities, payouts, and various strategies for maximizing=
 your experience with European Roulette.</p>


<div class=3D"wp-block-image">
<figure class=3D"aligncenter size-full"><img decoding=3D"async" loading=3D"=
lazy" width=3D"626" height=3D"376" src=3D"https://www.primedope.com/wp-cont=
ent/uploads/image-25.png" alt=3D"European Roulette Field" class=3D"wp-image=
-18073"></figure></div>


<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"types-of-bets-and-their-probabilities"=
>Types of Bets and Their Probabilities</h2>


<div class=3D"wp-block-image">
<figure class=3D"alignright size-full"><img decoding=3D"async" loading=3D"l=
azy" width=3D"453" height=3D"321" src=3D"https://www.primedope.com/wp-conte=
nt/uploads/image-26.png" alt=3D"Bet Types" class=3D"wp-image-18074"></figur=
e></div>


<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"1-straight-up-bet-single-number">1. St=
raight-Up Bet (Single Number)</h3>



<p><strong>Probability:</strong> 1/37 (2.70%)</p>



<p><strong>Payout:</strong> 35:1</p>



<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> Betting on a single number. This bet offer=
s the highest payout but also has the lowest probability of winning. To cal=
culate the probability, consider there is only one winning number out of 37=
.</p>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"2-split-bet-two-adjacent-numbers">2. S=
plit Bet (Two Adjacent Numbers)</h3>



<p><strong>Probability:</strong> 2/37 (5.41%)</p>



<p><strong>Payout:</strong> 17:1</p>



<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> Covers two numbers that are next to each o=
ther on the betting grid. The probability doubles that of a straight-up bet=
 as it includes two potential winning outcomes.</p>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"3-street-bet-three-numbers-in-a-row">3=
. Street Bet (Three Numbers in a Row)</h3>



<p><strong>Probability:</strong> 3/37 (8.11%)</p>



<p><strong>Payout:</strong> 11:1</p>



<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> This bet covers three consecutive numbers =
in a horizontal line. The probability increases to account for the three po=
tential winning numbers.</p>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"4-corner-bet-four-numbers">4. Corner B=
et (Four Numbers)</h3>



<p><strong>Probability:</strong> 4/37 (10.81%)</p>



<p><strong>Payout:</strong> 8:1</p>



<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> Covers four numbers in a square formation =
on the table layout. This bet has a higher probability than the street bet =
as it includes more numbers.</p>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"5-line-bet-six-numbers">5. Line Bet (S=
ix Numbers)</h3>



<p><strong>Probability:</strong> 6/37 (16.22%)</p>



<p><strong>Payout:</strong> 5:1</p>



<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> Covers six numbers across two adjacent row=
s. The probability is nearly one in six spins.</p>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"6-dozen-bet-12-numbers">6. Dozen Bet (=
12 Numbers)</h3>



<p><strong>Probability:</strong> 12/37 (32.43%)</p>



<p><strong>Payout:</strong> 2:1</p>



<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> Bets on the first, second, or third dozen =
numbers. With twelve numbers covered, the probability of winning is just un=
der one-third.</p>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"7-column-bet-12-numbers">7. Column Bet=
 (12 Numbers)</h3>



<p><strong>Probability:</strong> 12/37 (32.43%)</p>



<p><strong>Payout:</strong> 2:1</p>



<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> Similar to the dozen bet, this covers one =
of three vertical columns of twelve numbers each.</p>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"8-even-money-bets-red-black-odd-even-1=
-18-19-36"><strong>8. Even-Money Bets (Red/Black, Odd/Even, 1-18/19-36)</st=
rong></h3>



<p><strong>Probability:</strong> 18/37 (48.65%)</p>



<p><strong>Payout:</strong> 1:1</p>



<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> These bets cover half of the numbers on th=
e wheel, excluding zero. The probability is slightly less than 50% due to t=
he presence of the single zero.</p>



<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"house-edge-and-expected-return">House =
Edge and Expected Return</h2>



<ul>
<li><strong>House Edge:</strong> 2.70%
<ul>
<li><strong>Calculation:</strong> The house edge is derived from the single=
 zero on the wheel, which gives the house an advantage. With 37 slots, the =
edge is calculated as ( \frac{1}{37} =3D 2.70\% ).</li>
</ul>
</li>



<li><strong>Expected Return:</strong> 97.30%
<ul>
<li><strong>Explanation:</strong> For every $100 wagered, the theoretical r=
eturn is $97.30, reflecting the house edge. This expected return helps play=
ers understand their potential long-term losses.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>



<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"advanced-probability-calculations">Adv=
anced Probability Calculations</h2>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"probability-of-winning-at-least-once-i=
n-multiple-spins">Probability of Winning at Least Once in Multiple Spins</h=
3>



<p>To calculate the chance of winning at least once in 10 spins for a strai=
ght-up bet:</p>



<p>The probability of losing a single spin is 36/37 =3D 97.29%</p>



<p>Thus, losing all 10 spins is 75.26%</p>


<div class=3D"wp-block-image">
<figure class=3D"aligncenter"><img decoding=3D"async" src=3D"https://lh7-us=
.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXfeEY6wJnxwSy-f_9wJ7ybv7x3GZ8KscVJXFc7GJT=
0sAtcEugG3GpV3sV_m0NVj6hxJTm79MzrrTqT5chn4zrlD8ValpXPzXvGZDIJZL7bHnV6UFsG1U=
Aea2YOeOwsI1-EWTZBkMLUdspkOfRF0IWztF7vX?key=3DKqHLMz8_Hv_aSiaZFAEydg" alt=
=3D""></figure></div>


<p>Therefore, the probability of winning at least once is 24.74%</p>


<div class=3D"wp-block-image">
<figure class=3D"aligncenter"><img decoding=3D"async" src=3D"https://lh7-us=
